<subSubSection id="C3146527FF83E571531A80A16119FA55" lastPageId="67" lastPageNumber="184" pageId="66" pageNumber="183" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFF83E571531A80A16119FA55" blockId="66.[831,1437,1961,2085]" lastBlockId="67.[151,756,1353,1505]" lastPageId="67" lastPageNumber="184" pageId="66" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFF83E570531A80A160A5F875" bold="true" box="[831,942,1961,1985]" pageId="66" pageNumber="183">Comment</emphasis>
: The original description is based on a unique male from “ 
<collectingCountry id="F319763CFF83E57053EC80C16718F855" box="[969,1043,1993,2017]" name="Myanmar" pageId="66" pageNumber="183">Burma</collectingCountry>
: Ruby Mines” (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5DFF83E57054F080C1669AF855" author="CAMERON, M." box="[1237,1425,1993,2017]" pageId="66" pageNumber="183" refId="ref57482" refString="CAMERON, M. 1939 a: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae. Volume IV Parts I-II. - Sewell, R. B. S. (ed): The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. - London: 691 pp." type="book" year="1939">CAMERON 1939a</bibRefCitation>
). Cameron´s original subgeneric assignment was adopted also by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5DFF83E57053B88F026783F795" author="HLAVAC, P. &amp; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M." box="[925,1160,2057,2085]" pageId="66" pageNumber="183" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref57922" refString="HLAVAC, P.; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M. 2011: World catalogue of the species of the tribe Lomechusini (Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Zootaxa 3075: 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="2011">HLAVÁČ et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. An examination of the 
<typeStatus id="54B5880EFF82E57150B2824163FCFAD5" box="[151,247,1353,1377]" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">holotype</typeStatus>
, however, revealed that the specimen certainly does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFF82E571514D826262EDFA35" authority="sensu" authorityName="SenSU" box="[360,486,1386,1409]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFF82E571514D826262A9FA35" box="[360,418,1386,1409]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="184">Zyras</emphasis>
sensu
</taxonomicName>
strictu. In fact, based on external characters (antennal morphology, conspicuously slender maxillary palpi, punctation of the abdomen), the generic assignment is doubtful, too.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
